{"word":"ἐξαπόλλυμι","slug":"ἐξαπόλλυμι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐξαπόλλυμι</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-ολέσω</el>) (attic <el>-ολῶ</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to destroy utterly</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, with <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> 2 <el>ἐξαπόλωλα</el>, aor2 <el>ἐξαπωλόμην</el>: — <i>to perish utterly out of</i> a place, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to perish utterly</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}